6
00:02:20,733 --> 00:02:22,337
I just love the countryside.

7
00:02:22,478 --> 00:02:23,322
Bye!

8
00:02:23,337 --> 00:02:23,962
See ya!

9
00:02:24,232 --> 00:02:25,415
Let's go to your place!

10
00:02:25,714 --> 00:02:26,808
No way!

11
00:02:26,843 --> 00:02:28,188
Why not you jerk!

12
00:02:28,204 --> 00:02:29,164
Because!

13
00:02:29,311 --> 00:02:29,604
Come on.

14
00:02:29,629 --> 00:02:31,960
Hi Aiko, heard you got a bad report.

15
00:02:31,979 --> 00:02:34,366
Uh-huh, but I don't mind.

16
00:02:34,443 --> 00:02:35,229
How come?

17
00:02:35,348 --> 00:02:38,358
As soon as we get home, we're going
to my grandma's in the countryside.

18
00:02:38,824 --> 00:02:40,899
So it'll be ages before I get yelled at.

19
00:02:40,987 --> 00:02:42,100
Your lucky!

20
00:02:42,235 --> 00:02:44,165
Your going to the country side too?

21
00:02:44,341 --> 00:02:47,100
Yup, Nagano. How about you Taeko?

22
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:48,231
I don't know.

23
00:02:48,319 --> 00:02:49,724
Guess where I'm going.

24
00:02:49,726 --> 00:02:51,173
My dad bought a summer house.

25
00:02:51,198 --> 00:02:53,122
Wow! Amazing!

26
00:02:54,514 --> 00:02:57,912
Taeko, such a bad grade in math again?

27
00:02:58,980 --> 00:03:01,358
But science improved, did you notice?

28
00:03:02,090 --> 00:03:04,147
Hey mom, where are we going this summer?

29
00:03:04,380 --> 00:03:05,248
Nowhere.

30
00:03:06,271 --> 00:03:08,170
But I want you to take me somewhere.

31
00:03:08,930 --> 00:03:10,813
I can take you to a movie.

32
00:03:10,829 --> 00:03:12,959
The Grateful Crane is playing, isn't it?

33
00:03:13,573 --> 00:03:15,293
No, that's not what I mean.

34
00:03:15,456 --> 00:03:16,928
Take me to the country side.

35
00:03:16,944 --> 00:03:17,944
Country side?

36
00:03:18,005 --> 00:03:19,888
Yes, maybe grandma's village.

37
00:03:19,904 --> 00:03:21,280
Grandma lives here with us.

38
00:03:21,362 --> 00:03:23,108
Well then, what about grandpa's?

39
00:03:23,124 --> 00:03:24,311
He died remember?

40
00:03:24,530 --> 00:03:26,263
We don't have any relatives in the country,

41
00:03:26,419 --> 00:03:29,069
please don't ask me for things you know we don't have.

42
00:03:30,868 --> 00:03:33,621
Both my parents were born and razed in Tokyo.

43
00:03:33,845 --> 00:03:38,459
Unlike my friends, we didn't have any home
village we could easily visit out in the countryside.

44
00:03:38,972 --> 00:03:40,475
And even if we did...

45
00:03:42,679 --> 00:03:45,795
Going away now would be imposable,
everywhere would be all full up.

46
00:03:46,047 --> 00:03:47,491
I wanna go!

47
00:03:48,707 --> 00:03:49,975
There is the "Onoya"?

48
00:03:50,561 --> 00:03:52,154
We used to go there all the time.

49
00:03:52,170 --> 00:03:53,997
I'm sure they'd find a room for us.

50
00:03:53,999 --> 00:03:54,645
Don't you think...

51
00:03:54,660 --> 00:03:55,449
Sounds great!

52
00:03:55,465 --> 00:03:56,184
Lets go!

53
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:59,567
Yeah mom, that a great idea and Taeko's never been there.

54
00:03:59,814 --> 00:04:01,098
Huh, that's right.

55
00:04:01,114 --> 00:04:03,332
Hey, is it in the mountains... the sea?

56
00:04:04,152 --> 00:04:04,934
In Atami.

57
00:04:06,902 --> 00:04:07,806
Atami?

58
00:04:07,834 --> 00:04:10,468
Its fab and you get to take the bullet train.

59
00:04:10,845 --> 00:04:13,082
That's right, you'll love the bullet train.

60
00:04:16,555 --> 00:04:17,555
Atami...

61
00:04:17,656 --> 00:04:18,857
It's a lots of fun.

62
00:04:18,942 --> 00:04:20,755
There's all kinds of hot springs.

63
00:04:20,779 --> 00:04:23,903
Oh, but you know, the biggest one is the Roman Bath.

64
00:04:24,036 --> 00:04:24,786
She's right,

65
00:04:24,810 --> 00:04:26,925
and there's a whole lot of little ones as well.

66
00:04:27,176 --> 00:04:29,708
There's a mermaid bath and one called the Swan.

67
00:04:29,724 --> 00:04:31,661
Oh! That ones my favorite.

68
00:04:33,080 --> 00:04:34,091
A mermaid?

69
00:04:34,150 --> 00:04:36,302
Oh yeah. You might even see a real mermaid.

70
00:04:36,566 --> 00:04:38,410
And you just love hot springs.

71
00:04:38,435 --> 00:04:39,591
With mermaids.

72
00:04:39,607 --> 00:04:42,903
Well, your father has to work
so why don't the four of you go?

73
00:04:43,112 --> 00:04:43,724
Huh?!

74
00:04:44,958 --> 00:04:45,536
Uh.

75
00:04:45,613 --> 00:04:46,221
Oh.

76
00:04:47,825 --> 00:04:49,458
The four of us?

77
00:04:49,474 --> 00:04:50,520
Oh great.

78
00:04:57,772 --> 00:05:01,173
Your here every day Taeko, that's pretty impressive.

79
00:05:01,682 --> 00:05:03,688
All my friends have gone to the country.

80
00:05:06,437 --> 00:05:08,676
So ah, aren't you going anywhere?

81
00:05:09,192 --> 00:05:11,102
Yup', Atami.

82
00:05:11,884 --> 00:05:14,859
Atami? What are you going to do in Atami?

83
00:05:14,960 --> 00:05:16,587
Take hot springs baths.

84
00:05:18,389 --> 00:05:18,931
Oh.

85
00:05:20,751 --> 00:05:22,126
That's really good timing.

86
00:05:22,295 --> 00:05:25,889
Me and my family go away next week and
there won't be anyone here for a while.

87
00:05:26,428 --> 00:05:27,850
Have a great time in Atami.

88
00:05:27,878 --> 00:05:28,634
OK.

89
00:05:28,752 --> 00:05:29,834
See you later then.

90
00:05:32,662 --> 00:05:34,100
Okajima Residence. Hello.

91
00:05:34,834 --> 00:05:37,358
Hey Nanako, it's Taeko how are you.

92
00:05:37,928 --> 00:05:40,475
I'm heading up to the farm
today to see your husband's family.

93
00:05:40,563 --> 00:05:41,714
Need me to bring anything?

94
00:05:42,186 --> 00:05:43,905
Nothing in particular.

95
00:05:44,114 --> 00:05:46,834
Oh wait, maybe you could buy some cookies for Naoko.

96
00:05:46,850 --> 00:05:49,120
And tell her there from Morockometo and me.

97
00:05:49,412 --> 00:05:50,451
I'll pay you back.

98
00:05:50,453 --> 00:05:52,491
No problem. Don't worry about it.

99
00:05:52,788 --> 00:05:53,874
So, how's mom?

100
00:05:54,303 --> 00:05:55,530
She's out today.

101
00:05:56,068 --> 00:05:57,240
But she's mad at you.

102
00:05:57,484 --> 00:05:59,248
You wouldn't even meet that guy.

103
00:05:59,450 --> 00:06:03,530
It was a sure thing and all agreed.
She's said 27 and to old to be picky.

104
00:06:03,834 --> 00:06:06,321
Oh, that's all mom ever thinks about.

105
00:06:06,461 --> 00:06:09,105
True, but you could think about it a little bit more.

106
00:06:09,225 --> 00:06:10,465
You're not so young anymore.

107
00:06:10,527 --> 00:06:12,002
Oh, thanks a lot.

108
00:06:12,018 --> 00:06:12,910
Tae, your not old.

109
00:06:13,410 --> 00:06:16,985
But what's wrong with settling down
instead of doing all these wacky things.

110
00:06:17,300 --> 00:06:20,637
Did you really take a vacation
to work in the fields last year?

111
00:06:20,653 --> 00:06:24,458
Yup', harvesting rice. This year, I'm picking safflowers.

112
00:06:24,654 --> 00:06:25,575
Safflowers?

113
00:06:25,591 --> 00:06:29,606
Yes! Cause-a' you, I gots' me a fine farm family now.

114
00:06:30,194 --> 00:06:32,362
And they've adopted me as one of there own.

115
00:06:32,378 --> 00:06:33,520
Aw, give me a break.

116
00:06:34,324 --> 00:06:35,411
Sho' nuff.

117
00:06:36,248 --> 00:06:37,744
You don't get that much vacation.

118
00:06:37,876 --> 00:06:43,856
Don't stay in that drafty old house. Why not treat
yourself to a fancy hotel somewhere and relax, unwind

119
00:06:44,366 --> 00:06:46,666
you might even meet someone special up there.

120
00:06:46,999 --> 00:06:51,059
You can forget about that. And I
don't believe in mermaids anymore either.

121
00:06:51,247 --> 00:06:52,168
"Mermaids"?

122
00:06:52,513 --> 00:06:54,973
Oh yeah, right the bath in Atami.

123
00:06:55,974 --> 00:06:57,650
Are you still dwelling on that?

124
00:06:58,066 --> 00:07:00,398
Taeko, you still hang on to things don't you.

125
00:07:12,739 --> 00:07:15,739
My sisters, of didn't want to go anyplace like Atami.

126
00:07:16,079 --> 00:07:18,044
So, of course they didn't.

127
00:07:19,037 --> 00:07:21,243
Uh, grandma?

128
00:07:21,277 --> 00:07:22,649
Mm.. Mmm.

129
00:07:22,689 --> 00:07:24,362
Come on.

130
00:07:25,173 --> 00:07:27,429
Can we go to a bath now?

131
00:07:27,571 --> 00:07:29,437
We just got back from one.

132
00:07:29,828 --> 00:07:31,900
But that was only a little one.

133
00:07:31,916 --> 00:07:33,867
I was board out of my mind.

134
00:07:33,883 --> 00:07:35,195
So, I tried them all.

135
00:07:36,659 --> 00:07:37,992
The Grimm Brothers Bath.

136
00:07:39,174 --> 00:07:41,296
The Mermaid, The Lemon.

137
00:07:41,578 --> 00:07:43,101
The Purple Pansy Bath, and..

138
00:07:43,406 --> 00:07:46,078
When I got to the Roman Bath my head was spinning.

139
00:07:46,259 --> 00:07:48,268
It's huge!

140
00:07:53,872 --> 00:07:55,557
It's amazing...

141
00:08:05,275 --> 00:08:08,975
I staggered, I swooned, I almost drowned.

142
00:08:09,714 --> 00:08:12,545
The overnight trip I begged for was over.

143
00:08:12,918 --> 00:08:17,188
And awaiting me back home was
a long boring summer vacation.

144
00:08:29,367 --> 00:08:32,066
The other day, my sisters and I were reminiscing.

145
00:08:33,008 --> 00:08:35,816
I found myself finally telling them about it.

146
00:08:36,541 --> 00:08:40,628
We couldn't stop laughing as
the memories came flooding back.

147
00:08:45,847 --> 00:08:46,472
Cool.

148
00:08:47,889 --> 00:08:48,823
You ever tried one?

149
00:08:48,868 --> 00:08:49,894
Only from a tin.

150
00:08:51,277 --> 00:08:52,839
I'm the one who asked for it.

151
00:08:53,067 --> 00:08:53,956
Yeah, we know.

152
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:56,042
Dad, where'd you buy it?

153
00:08:56,602 --> 00:08:58,128
The Sembikiya in Ginza.

154
00:08:58,301 --> 00:08:59,964
It must have cost the earth.

155
00:09:01,212 --> 00:09:02,706
So, how do you eat it?

156
00:09:03,027 --> 00:09:04,269
Slice it into rings.

157
00:09:04,302 --> 00:09:05,386
Slice it how?

158
00:09:05,900 --> 00:09:06,378
Mm..

159
00:09:08,044 --> 00:09:08,769
I don't know.

160
00:09:10,638 --> 00:09:13,222
Did you ask at the store how we should serve it?

161
00:09:13,365 --> 00:09:13,878
Umm.

162
00:09:18,364 --> 00:09:20,441
Let's save it and have it Sunday.

163
00:09:20,835 --> 00:09:23,224
Huh? Why not now?!

164
00:09:23,517 --> 00:09:26,002
I think we should wait until we know how to serve it.

165
00:09:28,789 --> 00:09:29,916
I'll have a banana.

166
00:09:29,995 --> 00:09:30,970
Banana anyone?

167
00:09:30,972 --> 00:09:31,901
I want one.

168
00:09:35,854 --> 00:09:39,855
They certainly do have some strange
looking fruit in those hot countries.

169
00:09:43,019 --> 00:09:43,738
I'm home!

170
00:09:44,612 --> 00:09:46,979
I found out how to cut up the pineapple!

171
00:09:47,454 --> 00:09:48,355
Really?

172
00:09:54,854 --> 00:09:56,222
Watch your fingers Nanako.

173
00:09:56,238 --> 00:09:58,339
Wouldn't a carving knife work better?

174
00:10:10,325 --> 00:10:13,570
Wow! It smells so good.

175
00:10:14,179 --> 00:10:15,773
Pineapple.

176
00:10:23,791 --> 00:10:25,323
I can't wait.

177
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:28,721
Whad'ya know?

178
00:10:30,158 --> 00:10:31,705
Yaeko, get plates.

179
00:10:31,721 --> 00:10:33,754
Huh? Oh yeah, plates!

180
00:10:35,518 --> 00:10:36,580
We give thanks.

181
00:10:36,596 --> 00:10:38,062
We give thanks.

182
00:10:58,594 --> 00:10:59,760
It's hard.

183
00:11:04,908 --> 00:11:06,393
It's nothing to rave about.

184
00:11:06,747 --> 00:11:08,284
It's not very sweet is it?

185
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:10,674
It doesn't taste anything like what you can get in a can.

186
00:11:10,690 --> 00:11:13,143
Live as long as I have and you see everything.

187
00:11:19,426 --> 00:11:20,706
You can have mine Taeko.

188
00:11:20,924 --> 00:11:21,815
And mine too.

189
00:11:51,478 --> 00:11:52,969
It's good...

190
00:11:59,019 --> 00:12:01,312
Taeko, you don't have to eat all of it.

191
00:12:01,508 --> 00:12:02,461
You'll get sick.

192
00:12:11,882 --> 00:12:13,301
Oh well..

193
00:12:13,594 --> 00:12:15,074
That was a letdown.

194
00:12:17,998 --> 00:12:20,121
Bananas taste a lot better, don't they?

195
00:12:20,137 --> 00:12:21,348
You can say that again.

196
00:12:21,631 --> 00:12:24,402
I guess bananas are still the king of fruit.

197
00:12:24,734 --> 00:12:26,254
Time for a banana then.

198
00:12:52,459 --> 00:12:54,236
The king of fruits.

199
00:12:55,129 --> 00:12:56,791
The king of fruits..

200
00:12:57,026 --> 00:12:58,424
Was the banana.

201
00:13:03,560 --> 00:13:07,041
The year I fainted at the baths
and had my first pineapple...

202
00:13:07,337 --> 00:13:09,478
Was the year the Beatles came to Japan,

203
00:13:09,552 --> 00:13:11,830
starting the groups sounds craze.

204
00:13:12,599 --> 00:13:15,181
Everyone wanted to play the electric guitar.

205
00:13:19,674 --> 00:13:22,142
My sister Nanako, was a freshman in art school,

206
00:13:22,418 --> 00:13:24,541
and always up on the latest trends.

207
00:13:25,681 --> 00:13:29,041
Yum, Michelle right.. The Beatles' have such great lyrics.

208
00:13:29,065 --> 00:13:31,416
She was one of the first to wear a mini-skirt

209
00:13:31,744 --> 00:13:33,299
and like everyone else,

210
00:13:33,315 --> 00:13:37,463
soon figured out there was a right
way to avoid the wrong kind of stares.

211
00:13:38,580 --> 00:13:41,392
My other sister, Yaeko, was in
her second year of high school.

212
00:13:41,702 --> 00:13:42,931
"Super brainy."

213
00:13:43,822 --> 00:13:47,329
Still, I knew she was crazy.
About some Takarazuka actress.

214
00:13:47,345 --> 00:13:48,775
...you need to knock before coming in!

215
00:13:52,994 --> 00:13:55,010
When my sisters recall the good old days,

216
00:13:55,026 --> 00:13:57,658
it's mainly about fashions or pop stars.

217
00:13:57,984 --> 00:14:01,517
For them, 1966 was the high point of their youth.

218
00:14:02,236 --> 00:14:04,400
But for me, it was just for the grade.

219
00:14:05,119 --> 00:14:07,361
Bands like the Tigers and Julie

220
00:14:07,588 --> 00:14:09,260
wouldn't appear until years later.

221
00:14:09,674 --> 00:14:12,314
So, for me their discoveries of 1966

222
00:14:12,728 --> 00:14:15,502
were mainly going to school and coming home and...

223
00:14:15,518 --> 00:14:19,330
And then "my" essay was put up on the wall by my teacher.

224
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,564
Oh, that's wonderful.

225
00:14:22,158 --> 00:14:23,949
And then you know what he said mom?

226
00:14:23,965 --> 00:14:26,443
A book report this good should be read in the book club.

227
00:14:26,775 --> 00:14:28,916
Isn't that absolutely incredible?

228
00:14:29,681 --> 00:14:30,845
Well, isn't it?

229
00:14:31,255 --> 00:14:32,875
You didn't eat all your lunch again.

230
00:14:32,891 --> 00:14:33,314
Huh?

231
00:14:33,465 --> 00:14:35,478
Why do you hide the pickles in your bread?

232
00:14:35,903 --> 00:14:38,049
'Cause I really hate pickles.

233
00:14:38,261 --> 00:14:41,892
Now I've got to throw all of this away. What a waste.

234
00:14:42,465 --> 00:14:44,051
Your such a picky eater!

235
00:14:44,894 --> 00:14:47,094
I think it would be a whole lot better

236
00:14:47,286 --> 00:14:49,688
if you were a girl who ate what she is given

237
00:14:49,690 --> 00:14:53,231
instead of a girl whose essays are just
a little bit better than everyone else's.

238
00:15:08,326 --> 00:15:10,912
How do you drink that, its awful.

239
00:15:12,070 --> 00:15:13,954
I don't think the milks too bad,

240
00:15:14,138 --> 00:15:16,053
it's the radish and onions I hate.

241
00:15:16,591 --> 00:15:18,351
Me, I'm sticking to carrots.

242
00:15:18,367 --> 00:15:20,256
So, I'm going to have to drink the milk.

243
00:15:20,948 --> 00:15:23,722
It's stupid that we can only leave one thing on our plate?

244
00:15:23,738 --> 00:15:25,131
Who made this rule anyway?

245
00:15:25,744 --> 00:15:26,592
I'll drink it.

246
00:15:26,775 --> 00:15:28,151
Huh? You will!

247
00:15:28,343 --> 00:15:31,342
Next time you eat my radish and onions, OK?

248
00:15:32,023 --> 00:15:33,198
Um-hum, um-hum, um-hum.

249
00:15:39,944 --> 00:15:40,647
Thank you!

250
00:15:43,967 --> 00:15:44,481
Hey, don't...?

251
00:15:44,506 --> 00:15:46,155
We can leave one thing remember!

252
00:15:55,375 --> 00:15:57,444
That second bowls' a killer.

253
00:15:58,103 --> 00:16:00,538
Some people keep running in the hall,

254
00:16:00,754 --> 00:16:03,724
and there are some people I won't name who don't stop

255
00:16:03,876 --> 00:16:06,092
even when the hall monitor told them to.

256
00:16:06,334 --> 00:16:09,255
Nobody's gonna turn around and then walk back.

257
00:16:09,367 --> 00:16:11,795
You shouldn't really be running in the first place.

258
00:16:11,811 --> 00:16:13,037
Just don't do it.

259
00:16:13,053 --> 00:16:14,905
They're right. You could knock somebody over.

260
00:16:15,034 --> 00:16:19,252
Oh yeah, on the other hand if they ran
into you they'd just bounce right off.

261
00:16:19,268 --> 00:16:19,888
Stop!

262
00:16:19,903 --> 00:16:20,608
Boing.

263
00:16:22,517 --> 00:16:24,998
I don't know why everyone can't just walk in the halls.

264
00:16:25,014 --> 00:16:26,178
You know he's right.

265
00:16:26,194 --> 00:16:26,897
Please!

